<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
        <%- include('../Template-Engine/blog') %> 
</head>

<body>
        <%- include('../header.ejs')%>

                <main>
                        <div class="collection">
                                <div class="heading m-tb">
                                        <h1 class="flex justify-center blog-heding">10 Surefire Ways to Boost Your
                                                Windows Performance</h1>
                                </div>
                                <div class="overview margin-bottom">
                                        <p class="blog-text-overview margin-bottom">Is your Windows PC feeling sluggish?
                                                Are you tired of
                                                waiting for programs to load or files to open? Don't worry; you're not
                                                alone. Over time, as you
                                                use your computer, it can start to slow down due to various reasons such
                                                as too many background
                                                processes, outdated software, or cluttered storage. However, there's no
                                                need to panic. With a
                                                few simple tweaks and optimizations, you can significantly boost your
                                                Windows performance and
                                                breathe new life into your PC. Here are the top 10 ways to do just that:
                                        </p>
                                        <div class="blog-overview-image">
                                                <!-- <img src="/images/download.png" alt="">
                        <img src="/images/download.png" alt=""> -->
                                        </div>
                                </div>

                                <hr>
                                <section class="container margin-top">
                                        <div class="blog-step-1 margin-bottom">
                                                <h1 class="margin-bottom">Perform Disk Cleanup:</h1>
                                                <p class="bold margin-bottom ">step 1: <span
                                                                class="blog-text-overview normal">Press the Windows
                                                                key and type "Disk Cleanup" in the search bar.</span>
                                                </p>
                                                <p class="bold margin-bottom ">step 2: <span
                                                                class="blog-text-overview normal">Select the Disk
                                                                Cleanup app from the search results.</span></p>
                                                <p class="bold margin-bottom ">step 3: <span
                                                                class="blog-text-overview normal">Choose the drive
                                                                you want to clean up (usually C: drive) and click
                                                                OK.</span></p>
                                                <p class="bold margin-bottom ">step 4: <span
                                                                class="blog-text-overview normal">Disk Cleanup will
                                                                calculate how much space you can free up. Check the
                                                                boxes next to the types of files you
                                                                want to delete, then click OK.</span></p>
                                                <p class="bold margin-bottom ">step 5: <span
                                                                class="blog-text-overview normal">Confirm that you
                                                                want to delete the selected files.</span></p>
                                        </div>
                                        <hr>
                                        <div class="blog-step-2 margin-top-bottom">
                                                <h1 class="margin-bottom">Disable Startup Programs:</h1>
                                                <p class="bold margin-bottom ">step 1: <span
                                                                class="blog-text-overview normal">Right-click on
                                                                the taskbar and select Task Manager, or press Ctrl +
                                                                Shift + Esc to open it
                                                                directly.</span></p>
                                                <p class="bold margin-bottom ">step 2: <span
                                                                class="blog-text-overview normal">Go to the
                                                                "Startup" tab.</span></p>
                                                <p class="bold margin-bottom ">step 3: <span
                                                                class="blog-text-overview normal">You'll see a list
                                                                of programs that launch at startup. Right-click on any
                                                                unnecessary programs and select
                                                                "Disable".</span></p>
                                        </div>
                                        <hr>
                                        <div class="blog-step-3 margin-top-bottom">
                                                <h1 class="margin-bottom">Update Drivers:</h1>
                                                <p class="bold margin-bottom ">step 1: <span
                                                                class="blog-text-overview normal">Press the Windows
                                                                key and type "Device Manager" in the search bar.</span>
                                                </p>
                                                <p class="bold margin-bottom ">step 2: <span
                                                                class="blog-text-overview normal">Select Device
                                                                Manager from the search results.</span></p>
                                                <p class="bold margin-bottom ">step 3: <span
                                                                class="blog-text-overview normal">Expand the
                                                                categories to find the devices you want to update (e.g.,
                                                                Display adapters, Network
                                                                adapters).</span></p>
                                                <p class="bold margin-bottom ">step 4: <span
                                                                class="blog-text-overview normal">Right-click on
                                                                the device, select "Update driver", and follow the
                                                                prompts to update the driver.</span>
                                                </p>
                                        </div>
                                        <hr>
                                        <div class="blog-step-4 margin-top-bottom">
                                                <h1 class="margin-bottom">Upgrade Your Hardware:</h1>
                                                <p class="bold margin-bottom ">step 1: <span
                                                                class="blog-text-overview normal">Determine which
                                                                hardware components may be limiting your system's
                                                                performance (e.g., RAM, hard
                                                                drive).</span></p>
                                                <p class="bold margin-bottom ">step 2: <span
                                                                class="blog-text-overview normal">Purchase
                                                                compatible hardware upgrades.</span></p>
                                                <p class="bold margin-bottom ">step 3: <span
                                                                class="blog-text-overview normal">Follow the
                                                                manufacturer's instructions to install the new
                                                                hardware.</span></p>
                                        </div>
                                        <hr>
                                        <div class="blog-step-5 margin-top-bottom">
                                                <h1 class="margin-bottom">Optimize Power Settings:</h1>
                                                <p class="bold margin-bottom ">step 1: <span
                                                                class="blog-text-overview normal">Press the Windows
                                                                key and type "Power & Sleep settings" in the search
                                                                bar.</span></p>
                                                <p class="bold margin-bottom ">step 2: <span
                                                                class="blog-text-overview normal">Select Power &
                                                                Sleep settings from the search results.</span></p>
                                                <p class="bold margin-bottom ">step 3: <span
                                                                class="blog-text-overview normal">Choose
                                                                "Additional power settings" on the right side.</span>
                                                </p>
                                                <p class="bold margin-bottom ">step 4: <span
                                                                class="blog-text-overview normal">Select the High
                                                                Performance plan from the list of available
                                                                plans.</span></p>
                                        </div>
                                        <hr>
                                        <div class="blog-step-7 margin-top-bottom">
                                                <h1 class="margin-bottom">Run System Maintenance Tasks:</h1>
                                                <p class="bold margin-bottom ">step 1: <span
                                                                class="blog-text-overview normal">Press the Windows
                                                                key and type "Defragment and Optimize Drives" in the
                                                                search bar.</span></p>
                                                <p class="bold margin-bottom ">step 2: <span
                                                                class="blog-text-overview normal">Select Defragment
                                                                and Optimize Drives from the search results.</span></p>
                                                <p class="bold margin-bottom ">step 3: <span
                                                                class="blog-text-overview normal">Select the drive
                                                                you want to optimize and click Optimize.</span></p>
                                        </div>
                                        <hr>
                                        <div class="blog-step-8 margin-top-bottom">
                                                <h1 class="margin-bottom">Disable Visual Effects:</h1>
                                                <p class="bold margin-bottom ">step 1: <span
                                                                class="blog-text-overview normal">Press the Windows
                                                                key and type "Performance" in the search bar.</span></p>
                                                <p class="bold margin-bottom ">step 2: <span
                                                                class="blog-text-overview normal">Select "Adjust
                                                                the appearance and performance of Windows" from the
                                                                search results.</span></p>
                                                <p class="bold margin-bottom ">step 3: <span
                                                                class="blog-text-overview normal">In the
                                                                Performance Options window, select the "Adjust for best
                                                                performance" option or manually
                                                                uncheck specific visual effects you don't need.</span>
                                                </p>
                                        </div>
                                        <hr>
                                        <div class="blog-step-8 margin-top-bottom">
                                                <h1 class="margin-bottom">Install Antivirus Software:</h1>
                                                <p class="bold margin-bottom ">step 1: <span
                                                                class="blog-text-overview normal">Choose a
                                                                reputable antivirus software provider.</span></p>
                                                <p class="bold margin-bottom ">step 2: <span
                                                                class="blog-text-overview normal">Download and
                                                                install the antivirus software.</span></p>
                                                <p class="bold margin-bottom ">step 3: <span
                                                                class="blog-text-overview normal">Follow the setup
                                                                instructions to configure and run a full system
                                                                scan.</span></p>
                                        </div>
                                        <hr>
                                        <div class="blog-step-8 margin-top-bottom">
                                                <h1 class="margin-bottom">Optimize Virtual Memory:</h1>
                                                <p class="bold margin-bottom ">step 1: <span
                                                                class="blog-text-overview normal">Press the Windows
                                                                key and type "Advanced system settings" in the search
                                                                bar.</span></p>
                                                <p class="bold margin-bottom ">step 2: <span
                                                                class="blog-text-overview normal">Select View
                                                                advanced system settings from the search results</span>
                                                </p>
                                                <p class="bold margin-bottom ">step 3: <span
                                                                class="blog-text-overview normal">In the System
                                                                Properties window, click on the Advanced tab.</span></p>
                                                <p class="bold margin-bottom ">step 4: <span
                                                                class="blog-text-overview normal">Under the
                                                                Performance section, click Settings.</span></p>
                                                <p class="bold margin-bottom ">step 5: <span
                                                                class="blog-text-overview normal">In the
                                                                Performance Options window, go to the Advanced
                                                                tab.</span></p>
                                                <p class="bold margin-bottom ">step 6: <span
                                                                class="blog-text-overview normal">Under Virtual
                                                                memory, click Change.</span></p>
                                                <p class="bold margin-bottom ">step 7: <span
                                                                class="blog-text-overview normal">Uncheck
                                                                "Automatically manage paging file size for all
                                                                drives".</span></p>
                                                <p class="bold margin-bottom ">step 8: <span
                                                                class="blog-text-overview normal">Select the drive
                                                                you want to modify, choose "Custom size", and set the
                                                                Initial size and Maximum size
                                                                according to your system specifications.</span></p>
                                                <p class="blog-text-overview margin-top-bottom">In the "Initial size
                                                        (MB)" field, enter the
                                                        amount of space you want to allocate for the initial size of the
                                                        paging file. This value is
                                                        usually recommended to be 1.5 times your system's RAM size. For
                                                        example, if you have 8 GB of
                                                        RAM, you might enter 12000 MB (which is 8 GB x 1024).</p>
                                                <p class="blog-text-overview margin-top-bottom">In the "Maximum size
                                                        (MB)" field, enter the
                                                        maximum amount of space you want to allocate for the paging
                                                        file. This value depends on your
                                                        specific system requirements and available disk space. A common
                                                        recommendation is to set it
                                                        to double the size of your RAM or more, but you can also use the
                                                        "System managed size"
                                                        option if you're unsure.</p>
                                        </div>
                                        <hr>
                                        <div class="blog-step-8 margin-top-bottom">
                                                <h1 class="margin-bottom">Regularly Update Windows and Software:</h1>
                                                <p class="bold margin-bottom ">step 1: <span
                                                                class="blog-text-overview normal">Press the Windows key,
                                                                type "Windows Update" in the search bar, and select
                                                                Windows Update settings.</span></p>
                                                <p class="bold margin-bottom ">step 2: <span
                                                                class="blog-text-overview normal">Click on "Check for
                                                                updates" and install any available updates.</span></p>
                                                <p class="bold margin-bottom ">step 3: <span
                                                                class="blog-text-overview normal">For other software,
                                                                open each program and check for updates through their
                                                                respective settings or menus.</span></p>
                                        </div>
                                        <p class="blog-text-overview margin-top-bottom">Following these step-by-step
                                                instructions will help you optimize your Windows PC for better
                                                performance, ensuring a smoother and more responsive computing
                                                experience.</p>
                                </section>
                        </div>

                </main>


                <%- include('../footer.ejs') %>
</body>

</html>